# Documentation Rules

## Language

- All code documentation MUST be written in English
- This includes:
  - JSDoc comments
  - Inline comments
  - README files
  - API documentation
  - Component documentation
  - Type definitions documentation

## Documentation Style

- Use clear and concise language
- Document all public APIs and components
- Include examples when relevant
- Keep documentation up to date with code changes
- Use proper grammar and spelling

## Component Documentation

- Document props and their types
- Include usage examples
- Explain component behavior and side effects
- Document any dependencies or requirements

## Type Documentation

- Document complex types and interfaces
- Explain the purpose of each type
- Include examples for non-obvious use cases

## Code Comments

- Write meaningful comments that explain "why" not "what"
- Keep comments up to date with code changes
- Remove commented-out code
- Use TODO comments sparingly and include JIRA ticket numbers when relevant